Release Description

WinRAR is a 32-bit/64-bit Windows version of RAR Archiver, an archiver and archive manager. RAR files can usually compress content by 8 percent to 15 percent more than ZIP files can. Unicode is supported in archive filenames, allowing non-English filenames to be handled painlessly.
